# Canonical author identity.
#
# The same person appears under five spellings across two addresses, because a
# squash merge stamps the GitHub profile display name rather than the local git
# author name, and the profile name has changed over the life of the project.
# Both addresses are verified on the account and attribute correctly; this file
# only affects how git itself groups them, in shortlog, blame and log.
#
# No history is rewritten. Mapping by address alone covers every name variant
# that used it.

